What is RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)?
---------------------------------------------

RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) is an AI technique that allows a Large Language Model (LLM) like ChatGPT, Gemini, or Llama 
to search external knowledge (documents, PDFs, databases, websites, etc.) before generating an answer.

Instead of answering only from what it learned during training, the AI retrieves relevant information first and then generates an accurate answer.

=======

Simple Definition

RAG = Search + AI Answer

or

RAG = Retrieve Information + Generate Response

Why do we need RAG?

Imagine ChatGPT without RAG.

Question:

What is the leave policy in my company?

ChatGPT has never seen your company's private documents.

Without RAG:

AI
│
├── No access to your documents
├── Doesn't know company rules
└── Gives generic answer

Example answer

"Most companies provide 15-20 leave days."

This may be completely wrong.

With RAG

Question
      │
      ▼
Search Company Documents
      │
      ▼
Find Leave Policy PDF
      │
      ▼
Send relevant paragraphs to LLM
      │
      ▼
Generate accurate answer

Answer

According to your HR Policy Version 3.2, employees receive:

• 12 Casual Leaves
• 12 Sick Leaves
• 15 Earned Leaves

This answer is accurate because the AI looked at your document first.

