==========

Components of RAG
-----------------

| Component       | Purpose                                    |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| PDF             | Knowledge Source                           |
| Text Splitter   | Splits large documents into smaller chunks |
| Embedding Model | Converts text into vectors                 |
| Vector Database | Stores embeddings                          |
| Retriever       | Finds the most relevant chunks             |
| LLM             | Generates the final answer                 |


Technologies Used
=================

| Purpose    | Tools                                         |
| ---------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Embeddings | Sentence Transformers, OpenAI Embeddings, BGE |
| Vector DB  | FAISS, ChromaDB, Pinecone, Milvus             |
| LLM        | ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, Llama                |
| Framework  | LangChain, LlamaIndex, Haystack               |


Why Embeddings?

Traditional search looks for exact words.

Example

Question

How can I reset my password?

PDF says

Users may change their login credentials.

A keyword search might fail because "password" and "login credentials" are different words.

Embeddings capture meaning, so they recognize these are related and retrieve the correct document.

======

Benefits of RAG

✅ Uses your own documents

✅ More accurate answers

✅ Reduces hallucinations

✅ Keeps knowledge up to date

✅ No need to retrain the AI model when documents change

✅ Works with PDFs, Word files, Excel sheets, databases, websites, and APIs

=====

Limitations

❌ If the retrieved document is incorrect or outdated, the answer can also be incorrect.

❌ Poor document chunking can reduce retrieval quality.

❌ Low-quality embeddings may miss relevant information.

❌ Searching very large knowledge bases can increase response time.

