===

A simple analogy

Think of RAG like an open-book exam:

Without RAG: The student answers only from memory and may forget or guess.
With RAG: The student first opens the textbook, finds the relevant chapter, and then writes the answer.

The AI model is the student, your documents are the textbook, and the retrieval system (FAISS, ChromaDB, etc.) is the index that quickly finds the right page. 
This combination is what makes RAG so powerful for real-world business applications.

